#MEM id=rules source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Technical/dev/skills/design-and-build/vercel-react-best-practices/rules/advanced-event-handler-refs.md
M|rules|title: Store Event Handlers in Refs
M|rules|impact: LOW
M|rules|impactDescription: stable subscriptions
M|rules|tags: advanced, hooks, refs, event-handlers, optimization
M|rules|Store callbacks in refs when used in effects that shouldn't re-subscribe on callback changes.
M|rules|**Incorrect (re-subscribes on every render):**
M|rules|```tsx
M|rules|function useWindowEvent(event: string, handler: (e) => void) {
M|rules|useEffect(() => {
M|rules|window.addEventListener(event, handler)
M|rules|return () => window.removeEventListener(event, handler)
M|rules|}, [event, handler])
M|rules|}
M|rules|```
M|rules|**Correct (stable subscription):**
M|rules|```tsx
M|rules|function useWindowEvent(event: string, handler: (e) => void) {
M|rules|const handlerRef = useRef(handler)
M|rules|useEffect(() => {
M|rules|handlerRef.current = handler
M|rules|}, [handler])
M|rules|useEffect(() => {
M|rules|const listener = (e) => handlerRef.current(e)
M|rules|window.addEventListener(event, listener)
M|rules|return () => window.removeEventListener(event, listener)
M|rules|}, [event])
M|rules|}
M|rules|```
M|rules|**Alternative: use `useEffectEvent` if you're on latest React:**
M|rules|```tsx
M|rules|import { useEffectEvent } from 'react'
M|rules|function useWindowEvent(event: string, handler: (e) => void) {
M|rules|const onEvent = useEffectEvent(handler)
M|rules|useEffect(() => {
M|rules|window.addEventListener(event, onEvent)
M|rules|return () => window.removeEventListener(event, onEvent)
M|rules|}, [event])
M|rules|}
M|rules|```
M|rules|`useEffectEvent` provides a cleaner API for the same pattern: it creates a stable function reference that always calls the latest version of the handler.